    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A family of anionic polysaccharides that are obtained by alkaline extraction from some species of red seaweeds. There are three major types of carrageenan, which include iota-carrageenan (i-carrageenan), kappa-carrageenan (κ-carrageenan), and lambda-carrageenan (λ-carrageenan). In conservation, it is used as a hydrogel in paintings consolidation, among other uses.</Note_Text>
